Hi @imlison 

Just a quick glance on your code: when your status code is _not_ 2xx, your `new Promise()` never resolves/rejects, and so, does not invoke `finally`. You could try using `Promise.reject()` instead:

```
http.interceptors.response.use(
    response => {
        const res = response.data
        const code = res["code"]
        const message = res["message"]
        const payload = res["data"]
        if (code >= 200 && code < 300) {
            return Promise.resolve(payload)
        } else {
            const msg = `[${code}] ${message}`
            ElNotification({ type: "warning", message: msg})
            
            // See below using Promise.reject(). You can use Promise.resolve() too, 
            // depending on how you want to handle these cases
            return Promise.reject();
        }
    }, error => {
        ElMessage({message: error, type: "error", grouping: true})
        return Promise.reject(error)
    }
)
```

Btw, your question is about the implementation of Promise, and not an issue specific to Axios.

