The types say that the the object passed in for the request `onFulfilled` interceptor callback is a `AxiosRequestConfig`, which says that the `headers` property is a `RawAxiosRequestHeaders`. This is not actually true by the time the request callback is invoked. `headers` becomes an instance of `AxiosHeaders`.

https://github.com/axios/axios/blob/v1.x/lib/core/Axios.js#L83

`AxiosRequestConfig` could have another generic parameter for `headers`:

```typescript
export interface AxiosRequestConfig<D = any, H = RawAxiosRequestHeaders> {
  ...
  headers?: H;
  ...
}
```

Which then would allow `AxiosHeaders` to be used for the interceptors and `RawAxiosRequestHeaders` in other cases:

```typescript
export class Axios {
  ...
  interceptors: {
    request: AxiosInterceptorManager<AxiosRequestConfig<any, AxiosHeaders>>;
    response: AxiosInterceptorManager<AxiosResponse>;
  };
  ...
}
```

