@dallenbaldwin What if you needed to download a 100GB file?
As we know, large amounts of IO data should only be handled in streams, especially on a server with concurrent requests. You can't load everything into RAM, even if it fits within the line length limit.

 Set up Axios to return a stream, and just pipe it to a file.

```js
async function downloadFile(url, outputPath) {
  const response = await axios({
    method: 'get',
    url,
    responseType: 'stream',
  });

  await pipeline(
    response.data,            // Readable (Axios stream)
    fs.createWriteStream(outputPath) // Writable (file)
  );
}
```

