If I'm understanding the [NodeJS docs for exports and conditional exports](https://nodejs.dev/en/api/v18/packages/) properly, `require("axios/dist/node/axios.cjs")` should not work at all. For it to work, `package.json` would need to have:

``` json
{
  "exports": {
    "./dist/node/axios.cjs": "./dist/node/axios.cjs"
  }
}
```

As it currently stands, the only supported require paths are `require("axios")` and `require("axios/package.json")`. The former should point to `./dist/node/axios.cjs` in a non-browser target.

So in other words, you should be able to just use `require("axios")` to get the CJS file. `import "axios"` will get the ES Module file, and the readme needs to remove the reference to `require("axios/dist/node/axios.cjs")` as it's invalid with the current `package.json` (alternatively the `package.json` needs modification).

