After some research, I discovered that setting the correct content-type header value and including the MIME type of the image being sent solved the problem.

Here's a code snippet:

```
const formData = new FormData();
formData.append("image", {
  uri: imageUri,
  type: mime.getType(imageUri),
  name: imageUri.split("/").pop(),
});

const response = await axios.post(
  URL,
