In the code you provided, you are attempting to set the "Content-Type" header to "multipart/form-data" for all requests made using Axios. However, setting default headers in Axios is a feature, and there seems to be a misunderstanding in how it should be done.

Your first code block is mostly correct for setting default headers, but there is a minor issue with the header configuration. Here's the corrected code :

const axios = require('axios');

// Set config defaults when creating the instance
const instance = axios.create({
  headers: {
    'Content-Type': 'multipart/form-data'
  }
});

// Now, any request made using the 'instance' will have the default header.
instance.post('https://httpbin.org/post', { x: 1 }).then(({ data }) => console.log(data));

This code will set the "Content-Type" header to "multipart/form-data" for all requests made using the instance you've created. So, it's not a bug; it's a feature of Axios that allows you to set default headers for requests made through a specific instance.

