Hope this helps: We are currently using Node 16, we were facing a lot of socket hang up and ECONNRESET errors due to Axios. My solution was to mandatorily destroy old/stale agents at the same time making sure that a new agent was created before the old agent was destroyed(with a delay). We had to also make sure that critical cases like say in-flight requests weren't destroyed(Ex: critical actions like payment related, etc). We targeted the actions that had the most errors, added a protection mechanism for critical actions(Ex: If critical actions like payment related, etc are in flight do not destroy agent till the TTL expires). We also have a retry mechanism for requests failed with socket hang up / ECONNRESET / ECONNREFUSED errors with exponential backoffs with jitters to prevent thundering herd.
