@kentrh I ended up writing an axios request interceptor for this. If the current page base domain is the same as the domain of the requested url, we pass the header (and cookie via withCredentials!) along in the request. There's a note in there that if you're doing this for some generic library you should probably handle country-code second-level domains correctly. If you're not running your site/server on any of those domains, it doesn't matter.

The website hosted at _frontend_.**company.com** will still send along the XSRF cookie and header to POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH requests sent to _backend_.**company.com**, unless the actual axios call is made with manually passed in withCredentials or withXSRFToken (I don't want to block someone from setting these themselves).

```typescript
/**
 * Intercept requests and enable XSRF-TOKEN handling in axios if the request is an "unsafe method" and the SLD and
 * TLD of the current page url match the SLD and TLD of the request url. This doesn't handle country-code second-level
 * domains (e.g. company.co.uk) properly, in order to do this you should use a library to properly parse the domains.
 * Since we don't use any country-code second-level domains, and have proper content policies in place, we don't care!
 */
const xsrfTokenRequestInterceptor: RequestInterceptor = (request) => {
  try {
    const method = request.method?.toLowerCase();

    const methodRequiresCSRFProtection = method !== undefined && ['post', 'put', 'delete', 'patch'].includes(method);

    const parsedCurrentURL = new URL(window.location?.href);
    const parsedTargetURL = new URL(axios.getUri(request));

    const currentHostname = parsedCurrentURL.hostname.split('.').slice(-2).join('.');
    const targetHostname = parsedTargetURL.hostname.split('.').slice(-2).join('.');
    const baseDomainsMatch = currentHostname === targetHostname;

    // If settings are explicitly passed, use them, otherwise apply logic as determined by domain match
    if (request.withXSRFToken === undefined) {
      request.withXSRFToken = baseDomainsMatch && methodRequiresCSRFProtection;
    }

    if (request.withCredentials === undefined) {
      request.withCredentials = baseDomainsMatch;
    }
  } catch (error: any) {
    console.error('Skipping XSRF-TOKEN header logic in interceptor: ', error);
  }

  return request;
};

// Utilized like the following:
const instance = axios.create(finalAxiosConfig);
instance.interceptors.request.use(xsrfTokenRequestInterceptor);
```

