@vamsee9 

The issue originates from the `proxy-from-env@1.1.0` package, which Axios uses for environment-based proxy resolution. This package internally relies on the deprecated `url.parse()` API:

```js
// proxy-from-env/index.js (line 3)
var parseUrl = require('url').parse;
```
When Axios calls proxyFromEnv.getProxyForUrl(location) at [lib/adapters/http.js:183](https://github.com/axios/axios/blob/v1.x/lib/adapters/http.js#L183), it triggers the DEP0169 warning in Node.js 18+.

I've implemented a fix that replaces proxy-from-env with a custom WHATWG URL-based implementation. Would it be acceptable to submit a PR for this? I'm happy to make any adjustments based on maintainer feedback 😘

I don’t think it’s healthy for Axios to keep being exposed to issues originating from a transitive dependency. So I opened https://github.com/axios/axios/pull/7292 proposing we remove proxy-from-env and switch to an in-house implementation. In the long run, improving and maintaining a small, well-scoped internal proxy resolution layer inside Axios feels like the more sustainable option.

That said, I think the final call should be made by the maintainers — especially in terms of compatibility expectations, maintenance burden, and whether the trade-off is worth it for the project.

